Section: __list_insert_at

 Inserts an element at a given index in a list.
 RDI = list, RSI = index, RDX = element, returns RAX = new list.
 Path 1: count < capacity, in-place shift.
 Path 2: at heap top, grow + shift.
 Path 3: not at top, copy-with-gap + doubling.

  emit-list-insert-at-prologue : CodegenState -> HelpResult2
